article.headline: Morgan St. 33, Bethune-Cookman 9
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Byron Selby passed for two touchdowns and ran for another as Morgan St. defeated Bethune-Cookman 33-9 on Saturday. Bethune-Cookman (2-3) suffered five turnovers, including four interceptions, and managed a season-low 148 yards of offense. Selby's three-yard run with 4:41 to go in the third quarter broke a 9-9 halftime tie. His second TD toss, this one an 18-yarder to Robert Surratt, came with 15 seconds left in the third period. James Meade added a 21-yard field goal for Morgan St. (2-3) with 9:55 left in the final period, and Devan James finished the scoring with a 65-yard TD run with 4:17 remaining. Bethune-Cookman had scored first when James Monds returned 24 yards for a touchdown off a Morgan St. punt that had been blocked by teammate Nick Mayant. Lucas Esquivel's extra-point kick made it 7-0 with 3:09 left in the first quarter. Morgan St. set up its first score when Rupert Gill blocked a Bethune-Cookman punt to put the Bears on the Wildcat six-yard line. Two plays later Selby passed six yards to Roderick Wolfe in the end zone. But on the ensuing extra-point try by James Meade for Morgan St., Bethune-Cookman's Brandon Odom blocked the kick. Ben Ballard picked it up for the Wildcats and ran the length of the field to give the Wildcats two points and a 9-6 lead with 5:46 left in the first half. Meade's 35-yard field goal made it a 9-9 game at the half.
